uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.owl.util

Class OIdentity

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.model.CIdentity
      • uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.owl.util.OIdentity
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<OIdentity>

    public class OIdentity
extends CIdentity
implements java.lang.Comparable<OIdentity>
    Represents the identity for a frames-based object derived from an OWL construct of some type. When the source is a OWLNamedObject of some kind then the IRI can be taken as the identifier, with the label being either manually specified or heuristically-generated from the IRI fragment, via the KLabel-mechanism. Otherwise both identifier and label must be provided.

    Provides a compareTo(uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.owl.util.OIdentity) method based on the lexical values of the labels or, if the labels are identical, on the lexical values of the identifiers.
